# Doc hubs and plans — sync ritual (assistant)

## Non-negotiable automation (already in pre-commit)

- After any **`PLAN_*.md`** add/rename/move or **`PLANS_TODO.md`** table row change: **`python scripts/plans_hub_sync.py --write`** and **`python scripts/plans-stats.py --write`** as required by **`.cursor/rules/docs-plans.mdc`** and **CONTRIBUTING.md**. CI blocks drift via `--check`.
- Do not tell the operator the hub is “fresh” if those commands were not run when plans files changed.

## Manual hubs (agent must verify in the same PR)

- **`docs/MAP.md`** / **`docs/MAP.pt_BR.md`**: rows must point to existing paths; follow **ADR 0004** (no product-tier markdown links into `docs/plans/` from MAP—entry remains **docs/README**).
- **`docs/adr/README*.md`** + **`AGENTS.md`**: new **ADR NNNN** files require index rows and an updated **“Current last ADR”** line in **AGENTS.md** when that is the repo convention for the latest ADR.

## Skill

Full checklist: **`.cursor/skills/doc-hubs-plans-sync/SKILL.md`**.

## What this rule does **not** replace

- **Operator judgement** on what is “notable” sequencing (still update `PLANS_TODO` when reality shifts).
- **`private-git-sync`** / stacked private git (separate ritual).
